vision is a single screen based app.
the main screen is called the 'view'.
top left corner has the 'v' (vision brand) watermark. 
  clicking 'v' defaults to [vision] view.
    [vision] view is a curated gallery of the algorithms favorite drops.
    every drop (post) is a chance to go viral.
    drop count (drops) is how many times it drops on a new person.
top right corner is the visionary's corner.
  visionary's corner shows users profile picture as a drop down.
      includes follow and dm. 
    drop down menu moves diagonally to a 4/3 triangle of the screen.
      visionary's drop down is a scrollable profile view.
      tap visoinary's corner for dropdown.
      tap visionary's corner again for retract.
bottom right hand corner is the goldheart.
   goldhearts of each post reveal relative to the viewers interaction with it.
      i.e. if viewer looks at post for 22 secconds and gives a goldheart, goldheart will overlay at 22s.
        goldheart overlays become part of the post.
        viewers can toggle on/off goldheart section.
      each visionary or viewer can choose a proceed donation from each transaction.
        i.e. for every goldheart, comment, share, record; a protion of the transaction whether sent or recieved can bless another.
          default blessing goes to the indigenous people of colombia.
left of the goldheart is the comment.
  tapping the comment exposes the dropdown keyboard which extends from the top of the screen.
    when typed, comments appear below the keyboard.
    comment section of each post reveals relative to the viewers interaction with it.
      i.e. if viewer looks at post for 22 secconds and types a comment, comment will overlay at 22s.
        comment section becomes part of the post.
          viewers can toggle on/off comment section.
left of the comment is the 'V' (vision pyramid logo).
  'V' takes the user to camera or media access.
    choose between take photo, video, or interact.
      interact allows user to create new content from posted content.
    
